{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"What I want to talk about today is one idea."},{"time":3000,"text":"It's an idea for a new kind of school,"},{"time":5000,"text":"which turns on its head much of our conventional thinking"},{"time":8000,"text":"about what schools are for and how they work."},{"time":10000,"text":"And it might just be coming to a neighborhood near you soon."},{"time":13000,"text":"Where it comes from"},{"time":15000,"text":"is an organization called the Young Foundation,"},{"time":17000,"text":"which, over many decades,"},{"time":19000,"text":"has come up with many innovations in education, like the Open University"},{"time":22000,"text":"and things like Extended Schools,"},{"time":24000,"text":"Schools for Social Entrepreneurs, Summer Universities"},{"time":27000,"text":"and the School of Everything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29000,"text":"And about five years ago, we asked"},{"time":31000,"text":"what was the most important need for innovation"},{"time":33000,"text":"in schooling here in the U.K."},{"time":36000,"text":"And we felt the most important priority"},{"time":38000,"text":"was to bring together two sets of problems."},{"time":40000,"text":"One was large numbers of bored teenagers"},{"time":42000,"text":"who just didn't like school,"},{"time":44000,"text":"couldn't see any relationship between what they learned in school"},{"time":46000,"text":"and future jobs."},{"time":48000,"text":"And employers who kept complaining"},{"time":50000,"text":"that the kids coming out of school weren't actually ready for real work,"},{"time":53000,"text":"didn't have the right attitudes and experience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55000,"text":"And so we try to ask:"},{"time":57000,"text":"What kind of school would have the teenagers fighting to get in,"},{"time":59000,"text":"not fighting to stay out?"},{"time":62000,"text":"And after hundreds of conversations"},{"time":64000,"text":"with teenagers and teachers and parents"},{"time":66000,"text":"and employers and schools"},{"time":68000,"text":"from Paraguay to Australia,"},{"time":70000,"text":"and looking at some of the academic research,"},{"time":72000,"text":"which showed the importance"},{"time":74000,"text":"of what's now called non-cognitive skills --"},{"time":76000,"text":"the skills of motivation, resilience --"},{"time":79000,"text":"and that these are as important"},{"time":81000,"text":"as the cognitive skills -- formal academic skills --"},{"time":83000,"text":"we came up with an answer, a very simple answer in a way,"},{"time":86000,"text":"which we called the Studio School."},{"time":88000,"text":"And we called it a studio school"},{"time":90000,"text":"to go back to the original idea of a studio in the Renaissance"},{"time":94000,"text":"where work and learning are integrated."},{"time":96000,"text":"You work by learning,"},{"time":98000,"text":"and you learn by working."},{"time":100000,"text":"And the design we came up with had the following characteristics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":103000,"text":"First of all, we wanted small schools --"},{"time":105000,"text":"about 300, 400 pupils --"},{"time":107000,"text":"14 to 19 year-olds,"},{"time":109000,"text":"and critically, about 80 percent of the curriculum done"},{"time":112000,"text":"not through sitting in classrooms,"},{"time":114000,"text":"but through real-life, practical projects,"},{"time":116000,"text":"working on commission"},{"time":118000,"text":"to businesses, NGO's and others."},{"time":120000,"text":"That every pupil would have a coach, as well as teachers,"},{"time":123000,"text":"who would have timetables"},{"time":125000,"text":"much more like a work environment in a business."},{"time":127000,"text":"And all of this will be done within the public system,"},{"time":129000,"text":"funded by public money,"},{"time":131000,"text":"but independently run."},{"time":133000,"text":"And all at no extra cost, no selection,"},{"time":136000,"text":"and allowing the pupils the route into university,"},{"time":139000,"text":"even if many of them would want to become entrepreneurs"},{"time":142000,"text":"and have manual jobs as well."},{"time":144000,"text":"Underlying it was some very simple ideas"},{"time":147000,"text":"that large numbers of teenagers learn best by doing things,"},{"time":150000,"text":"they learn best in teams"},{"time":152000,"text":"and they learn best by doing things for real --"},{"time":155000,"text":"all the opposite of what mainstream schooling"},{"time":157000,"text":"actually does."}]},{"cues":[{"time":159000,"text":"Now that was a nice idea,"},{"time":161000,"text":"so we moved into the rapid prototyping phase."},{"time":164000,"text":"We tried it out,"},{"time":166000,"text":"first in Luton --"},{"time":168000,"text":"famous for its airport and not much else, I fear --"},{"time":170000,"text":"and in Blackpool -- famous for its beaches and leisure."},{"time":173000,"text":"And what we found -- and we got quite a lot of things wrong"},{"time":175000,"text":"and then improved them --"},{"time":177000,"text":"but we found that the young people loved it."},{"time":179000,"text":"They found it much more motivational, much more exciting"},{"time":182000,"text":"than traditional education."},{"time":184000,"text":"And perhaps most important of all,"},{"time":186000,"text":"two years later when the exam results came through,"},{"time":189000,"text":"the pupils who had been put on these field trials"},{"time":191000,"text":"who were in the lowest performing groups"},{"time":193000,"text":"had jumped right to the top --"},{"time":195000,"text":"in fact, pretty much at the top decile of performance"},{"time":198000,"text":"in terms of GCSE's,"},{"time":200000,"text":"which is the British marking system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203000,"text":"Now not surprisingly,"},{"time":205000,"text":"that influenced some people to think we were onto something."},{"time":208000,"text":"The minister of education"},{"time":210000,"text":"down south in London"},{"time":212000,"text":"described himself as a \"big fan.\""},{"time":214000,"text":"And the business organizations thought we were onto something"},{"time":217000,"text":"in terms of a way of preparing children much better"},{"time":219000,"text":"for real-life work today."},{"time":221000,"text":"And indeed, the head of the Chambers of Commerce"},{"time":223000,"text":"is now the chairman of the Studio Schools Trust"},{"time":226000,"text":"and helping it, not just with big businesses,"},{"time":229000,"text":"but small businesses all over the country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232000,"text":"We started with two schools."},{"time":234000,"text":"That's grown this year to about 10."},{"time":236000,"text":"And next year, we're expecting about 35 schools"},{"time":239000,"text":"open across England,"},{"time":241000,"text":"and another 40 areas"},{"time":243000,"text":"want to have their own schools opening --"},{"time":245000,"text":"a pretty rapid spread"},{"time":247000,"text":"of this idea."},{"time":249000,"text":"Interestingly,"},{"time":251000,"text":"it's happened almost entirely without media coverage."},{"time":254000,"text":"It's happened almost entirely without big money behind it."},{"time":258000,"text":"It spread almost entirely through word of mouth, virally,"},{"time":262000,"text":"across teachers, parents,"},{"time":264000,"text":"people involved in education."},{"time":266000,"text":"And it spread because of the power of an idea --"},{"time":268000,"text":"so the very, very simple idea"},{"time":270000,"text":"about turning education on its head"},{"time":272000,"text":"and putting the things which were marginal,"},{"time":275000,"text":"things like working in teams, doing practical projects,"},{"time":278000,"text":"and putting them right at the heart of learning,"},{"time":281000,"text":"rather than on the edges."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284000,"text":"Now there's a whole set of new schools"},{"time":286000,"text":"opening up this autumn."},{"time":288000,"text":"This is one from Yorkshire"},{"time":290000,"text":"where, in fact, my nephew, I hope, will be able to attend it."},{"time":293000,"text":"And this one is focused"},{"time":295000,"text":"on creative and media industries."},{"time":297000,"text":"Other ones have a focus on health care,"},{"time":299000,"text":"tourism, engineering"},{"time":301000,"text":"and other fields."}]},{"cues":[{"time":303000,"text":"We think we're onto something."},{"time":305000,"text":"It's not perfect yet,"},{"time":307000,"text":"but we think this is one idea"},{"time":309000,"text":"which can transform the lives"},{"time":311000,"text":"of thousands, possibly millions, of teenagers"},{"time":313000,"text":"who are really bored by schooling."},{"time":315000,"text":"It doesn't animate them."},{"time":317000,"text":"They're not like all of you who can sit in rows"},{"time":320000,"text":"and hear things said to you for hour after hour."},{"time":323000,"text":"They want to do things, they want to get their hands dirty,"},{"time":326000,"text":"they want education to be for real."},{"time":329000,"text":"And my hope is that some of you out there"},{"time":331000,"text":"may be able to help us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":333000,"text":"We feel we're on the beginning of a journey"},{"time":336000,"text":"of experiment and improvement"},{"time":338000,"text":"to turn the Studio School idea"},{"time":340000,"text":"into something which is present,"},{"time":343000,"text":"not as a universal answer for every child,"},{"time":345000,"text":"but at least as an answer for some children in every part of the world."},{"time":348000,"text":"And I hope that a few of you at least can help us make that happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":353000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}